cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.SY, cs.DS, cs.NI 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper investigates different forms of multi-group connectivity and their implications on information propagation and consensus in networks. This falls under the domain of social and information networks. 
2. cs.SD (Software Engineering) - The paper proposes generative models to generate different multi-group connectivity modalities. This involves software engineering techniques for developing models. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper evaluates the performance of different connectivity structures in terms of convergence times and steady state deviations. This falls under the domain of systems and control. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses different types of connectivity structures and their properties, which is related to data structures and algorithms. 
5. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper investigates the implications of different connectivity structures on information propagation in networks, which is related to networking and internet architecture.
